DataElement.preferredName: Temporomandibular Joint Disorder Mild Pain Percentage Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: a numerical quantity measured or assigned or computed that is a fraction or ratio with 100 understood as the denominator related to the sensation of discomfort from any condition affecting the anatomic and functional characteristics of the temporomandibular joint that is not severe or strong.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the sensation of discomfort from any condition affecting the anatomic and functional characteristics of the temporomandibular joint that is not severe or strong.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Any condition affecting the anatomic and functional characteristics of the temporomandibular joint.

Concepts.definition: A disorder that affects the masticatory muscles and temporomandibular joint.

Property.preferredDefinition: Not severe or strong; far from extreme; not serious enough to endanger life.:An unpleasant sensation induced by noxious stimuli and generally received by specialized nerve endings.

Concepts.definition: Gentle or temperate in nature or degree.
The sensation of discomfort, distress, or agony, resulting from the stimulation of specialized nerve endings.
